The Armenian Church and the Georgian Church are among the oldest Christian churches in the world [source not specified 936 days] and play an important role in preserving the national identity of these peoples, who have been under foreign rule over the past centuries (Turks, Persians, Russians). Lake Sevan is one of the largest lakes in the region. In the Caucasus, there is one of the highest waterfalls in Russia - the Zeygalan waterfall in North Ossetia in the Midagrabindon river valley. Its height is about 600 m.

The direction of the flow of rivers in the Caucasus Mountains is predominantly radial. The rivers originating in the Caucasus belong to the basins of the Black, Azov and Caspian Seas.